{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "GitHub Release Notificator",
    "description": "API collection for testing the GitHub Release Notification service.\n\n## Quick Start\n1. Set the `baseUrl` variable (default: http://localhost:3000)\n2. Set `apiKey` only if authentication is enabled\n3. Run \"Subscribe\" first, then check email and copy `confirmToken` from the confirmation link\n4. Confirm subscription using \"Confirm Subscription\"\n5. Copy `unsubscribeToken` from the confirmation email (token shown as plain text) and use it in \"Unsubscribe\"\n\n## Variables\n- `baseUrl` — server URL\n- `apiKey` — X-API-Key value (leave empty if auth disabled)\n- `email` — test email address\n- `repo` — GitHub repo in owner/repo format\n- `confirmToken` — token from confirmation email link\n- `unsubscribeToken` — unsubscribe token from email text",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "apiKey",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "email",
      "value": "olegchaplia2006@gmail.com",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "repo",
      "value": "nodejs/node",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "confirmToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "unsubscribeToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "apikey",
    "apikey": [
      {
        "key": "key",
        "value": "X-API-Key",
        "type": "string"
      },
      {
        "key": "value",
        "value": "{{apiKey}}",
        "type": "string"
      },
      {
        "key": "in",
        "value": "header",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health Check",
      "request": {
        "auth": {
          "type": "noauth"
        },
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["health"]
        },
        "description": "Health check endpoint. Does NOT require API key.\n\nReturns `{ status: \"ok\", timestamp: \"...\" }`"
      },
      "response": [],
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "pm.test('Status is ok', () => {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('ok');",
              "    pm.expect(json.timestamp).to.be.a('string');",
              "});"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Subscription Flow",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Subscribe (JSON)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n    \"repo\": \"{{repo}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/subscribe",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "subscribe"]
            },
            "description": "Subscribe an email to release notifications for a GitHub repo.\n\n**Happy path:** Returns 200 + sends confirmation email.\n\nCheck your inbox for the confirmation link — copy the token UUID from the URL."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns success message', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.message).to.include('Confirmation email sent');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "1b. Subscribe (form-urlencoded)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "email", "value": "{{email}}", "type": "text" },
                { "key": "repo", "value": "facebook/react", "type": "text" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/subscribe",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "subscribe"]
            },
            "description": "Same endpoint but using form-urlencoded body (as per Swagger spec)."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Confirm Subscription",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/confirm/{{confirmToken}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "confirm", "{{confirmToken}}"]
            },
            "description": "Confirm subscription using the token from the confirmation email.\n\nNote: this endpoint can return HTML in browser mode, so Postman explicitly requests JSON via `Accept: application/json`.\n\n**How to get the token:**\n1. Check your email after subscribing\n2. Copy the UUID from the confirmation link URL\n3. Paste it into the `confirmToken` collection variable"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns confirmed message', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.message).to.include('confirmed');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "3. Get Subscriptions",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/subscriptions?email={{email}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "subscriptions"],
              "query": [{ "key": "email", "value": "{{email}}" }]
            },
            "description": "List all subscriptions for the given email.\n\nReturns an array of `{ email, repo, confirmed, last_seen_tag }`."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns array', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Each item has required fields', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (json.length > 0) {",
                  "        pm.expect(json[0]).to.have.property('email');",
                  "        pm.expect(json[0]).to.have.property('repo');",
                  "        pm.expect(json[0]).to.have.property('confirmed');",
                  "        pm.expect(json[0]).to.have.property('last_seen_tag');",
                  "    }",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "4. Unsubscribe",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/unsubscribe/{{unsubscribeToken}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "unsubscribe", "{{unsubscribeToken}}"]
            },
            "description": "Unsubscribe using token.\n\nNote: this endpoint can return HTML in browser mode, so Postman explicitly requests JSON via `Accept: application/json`.\n\n**How to get the token:**\nCopy `Unsubscribe token` from the confirmation email and set `unsubscribeToken`."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns unsubscribed message', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.message).to.include('Unsubscribed');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
